cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper presents a technique for training deep neural networks with noisy labels, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on image datasets, which further supports the likelihood of cs.CV. The paper also discusses the use of a softmax layer, which is commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks, suggesting a possible connection to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper uses dropout regularization, which is a common technique in neural network optimization, suggesting a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
